'''Sofa painting''' is a [[pejorative]] term for paintings that match a color scheme or match a sofa. However, an exhibition of Sofa art at the [[Knoxville Museum of Art]] proved that art made to go over the sofa could also communicate highly charged artistic messages.

The [[Bernice Steinbaum Gallery]] in [[Miami, Florida]] organized the exhibition, entitled: A Painting for Over the Sofa  (that's not necessarily a painting).

